race.description: Join Godolphin School Holiday Internship Maiden
race.comment: KAZARU (9) resumes for her second campaign having shown good ability as a 2yo. The debut effort was just fair before improving rapidly to place in Listed company at Morphettville, not far away in a G3 before a break. Like her at this trip fresh, she looks well placed back to maiden grade. BOOMEROO (4) was just fair on debut at Geelong when well supported, racing greenly to finish fourth. Willing to give another chance with that experience to count for plenty. ROSE OF CHURCHILL (10) is a filly by Churchill on debut for the Hayes yard. She's won a jump out leading in and should have plenty to offer. DIHHERI (7) was solid on debut in a handy maiden at Geelong over 1114m, now stepping up in trip which should suit. She can track the speed and take beating. BALTIC BLIZZARD (1) ran well on debut at Donald and has claims with improvement.
